FBIS4-16525 "drsov074_e_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Yeltsin, Kravchuk Agree To Share Black Sea Fleet Yeltsin, Kravchuk Agree To Share Black Sea Fleet AU1504162394 Paris AFP in English 1613 GMT 15 Apr 94 AU1504162394 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Moscow, 15 April (AFP) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk signed a deal Friday [15 April] to share out the disputed Black Sea Fleet on a 50-50 basis. But the agreement states Ukraine will use only between 15 percent and 20 percent of the fleet for its own purposes and will lease the remainder of its share to Russia, Ukrainian Defence Minister Vitaliy Radetsky said at a press conference.
